main event: An unidentified flying object resembling a V-2 rocket was reported in Arnhem, Holland on 20 July 1948, seen intermittently through clouds.
interesting points: The reported object had two decks and no wings,It was said to travel at supersonic speeds comparable to the V-2 rocket,It was observed four times through clouds by the chief of KLM and his daughter, There is skepticism about the reliability of the sighting, The incident occurred just four days before the famous Chiles-Whitted ship sighting.
sighted object: a long, cylindrical object resembling a rod or tube
witness description: The chief of the fleet of KLM and his daughter
